WEBVTT

00:01.135 --> 00:02.170
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Welcome back, friends.

00:02.203 --> 00:04.072
When we left our Jane,
she'd rekindled things

00:04.105 --> 00:06.107
with her first love, Adam.

00:06.140 --> 00:07.541
I am all in, Jane.

00:07.575 --> 00:10.378
So, yeah.
They were pretty smitten.

00:10.411 --> 00:12.080
And speaking of smitten,

00:12.113 --> 00:13.547
Jane's father Rogelio
had finally married

00:13.581 --> 00:15.283
her mother Xiomara.

00:15.316 --> 00:16.550
Only complication,

00:16.584 --> 00:18.419
he had a baby with Darci.

00:18.452 --> 00:20.321
And they named her...

00:20.354 --> 00:21.455
Well, I'll let him explain.

00:21.489 --> 00:22.723
First name, Baby.

00:22.756 --> 00:25.159
JANE:
My baby sister, Baby.

00:25.193 --> 00:26.327
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Yeah. And complicating that...

00:26.360 --> 00:27.328
Oh.

00:27.361 --> 00:29.630
...Darci started dating
his rival Esteban.

00:29.663 --> 00:32.066
I know. Straight out
of a telenovela, right?

00:32.100 --> 00:33.567
Which makes sense,
because Rogelio

00:33.601 --> 00:35.569
was a huge telenovela star.

00:35.603 --> 00:37.738
Though right now, he was
playing someone very tiny,

00:37.771 --> 00:39.473
who was swallowed
by his love interest,

00:39.507 --> 00:41.475
and was currently stuck
inside her body.

00:41.509 --> 00:42.376
Just go with it, okay?

00:42.410 --> 00:44.412
And speaking
of star-crossed lovers,

00:44.445 --> 00:46.547
Jane and Rafael
were currently estranged.

00:46.580 --> 00:49.450
See, he'd lost all his money,
and so he was scheming

00:49.483 --> 00:51.252
against his sister Luisa
to get his hotel back.

00:51.285 --> 00:54.122
For the last time,
I am doing this for my family!

00:54.155 --> 00:57.558
And as for Luisa, well,
she made a new friend, Carl.

00:57.591 --> 00:59.427
Only problem...
Dr. Luisa introduced me

00:59.460 --> 01:00.828
to her friend Carl,

01:00.861 --> 01:02.796
but there was no one there.

01:02.830 --> 01:05.333
So, yeah, Luisa
was definitely struggling.

01:05.366 --> 01:08.336
But Raf didn't know that.
He just wanted his hotel back.

01:08.369 --> 01:11.372
So he got into bed with hotel
financier Katherine Cortes.

01:11.405 --> 01:14.475
Literally. But he had a change
of heart about using her.

01:14.508 --> 01:17.345
And well, the consequences
came fast and furious.

01:17.378 --> 01:19.313
(tires screech)
I know.

01:19.347 --> 01:21.782
OMG, right? So let's dive in.

01:22.850 --> 01:24.518
Ah, friends.

01:24.552 --> 01:28.122
As you well know,
our Jane played many roles.

01:28.156 --> 01:31.225
And so, she had many labels.

01:31.259 --> 01:33.361
She was a mother.

01:33.394 --> 01:35.563
She was a lover.

01:35.596 --> 01:38.766
She was a writer, of course.

01:38.799 --> 01:41.302
But before she was
any of those things,

01:41.335 --> 01:43.904
she was a best friend.

01:43.937 --> 01:45.439
To Lina.

01:45.473 --> 01:46.674
Like my new hat?

01:46.707 --> 01:49.843
I stole it
from my sisters.

01:49.877 --> 01:52.413
You're gonna get
in so much trouble.

01:52.446 --> 01:54.515
(laughs)
NARRATOR: Of course, of the two,

01:54.548 --> 01:56.384
Lina was the bold one.

01:56.417 --> 01:58.419
She was adventurous.

01:58.452 --> 02:00.454
Want me to teach you
how to put on eye makeup?

02:00.488 --> 02:02.656
Yeah. But no wings.

02:02.690 --> 02:03.857
Then what's even the point?

02:03.891 --> 02:05.326
(sighs)

02:05.359 --> 02:07.361
The kind of person
who went for it.

02:07.395 --> 02:08.496
(quietly):
Kiss him.

02:09.663 --> 02:11.199
Which is why Jane knew

02:11.232 --> 02:12.666
her bachelorette party
had to be...

02:12.700 --> 02:15.236
A 1930s murder mystery theme?

02:15.269 --> 02:16.470
Really?

02:16.504 --> 02:18.306
I know. I was confused, too.

02:18.339 --> 02:19.940
I had our favorite stripper
on hold.

02:19.973 --> 02:21.742
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
He's my favorite, too.

02:25.379 --> 02:28.616
But, apparently, this is
what Lina and Danny want.

02:28.649 --> 02:31.485
So, I will make it
totally perfect.

02:31.519 --> 02:34.655
Because that is my solemn duty
as Lina's lifetime BFF.

02:34.688 --> 02:35.689
Oh, no.

02:35.723 --> 02:36.824
Oh, don't tell me

02:36.857 --> 02:37.958
that Dad can't get the costumes.

02:37.991 --> 02:39.727
No. Sorry.

02:39.760 --> 02:41.829
I just realized
I forgot to take the pill.

02:41.862 --> 02:43.664
Again? Why are you even
still on the pill?

02:43.697 --> 02:45.266
There are so many other options.

02:45.299 --> 02:46.734
The ring, the shot,
the patch, the cap.

02:46.767 --> 02:48.702
Look at you, Planned Parenthood.

02:48.736 --> 02:50.371
Thank you.
(laughs)

02:50.404 --> 02:51.739
Anyway, I've tried a few.

02:51.772 --> 02:53.741
Your dad just wants
to pull out, but...

02:53.774 --> 02:56.444
Oh. Okay. All right.
I'm gonna get going.

02:56.477 --> 02:59.280
Please tell Dad thank you
for the costumes and the props.

02:59.313 --> 03:02.450
(phone ringing)
Oh.

03:02.483 --> 03:04.985
(scoffs)

03:05.018 --> 03:07.555
Petra?
Everything's fine.
There's nothing to worry about.

03:07.588 --> 03:09.423
What do you mean?
Worry about what?
I just said there's nothing

03:09.457 --> 03:11.992
to worry about.
Well, that's a really weird way
to start a phone call.

03:12.025 --> 03:14.762
Rafael was in a little
car accident.
What?

03:14.795 --> 03:16.530
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Little?

03:16.564 --> 03:18.432
He looks like he was hit
by a Mack truck.

03:18.466 --> 03:20.868
Or, say, a late model sedan.

03:20.901 --> 03:21.869
But he's fine. Truly.

03:21.902 --> 03:23.837
Uh, actually, we're just
about to get discharged,

03:23.871 --> 03:25.539
so I'm just letting you know.
Okay.

03:25.573 --> 03:26.474
Well, tell him...

03:26.507 --> 03:28.909
I'm glad he's okay.
I will.

03:28.942 --> 03:32.513
I'm telling you,
it wasn't an accident.

03:32.546 --> 03:34.448
Oh, I'm sure. I mean,
you basically told Katherine

03:34.482 --> 03:36.284
you were using her
before the deal closed.

03:36.317 --> 03:37.418
What were you thinking?

03:37.451 --> 03:39.453
I just couldn't
go through with it.

03:40.854 --> 03:42.490
Oh.

03:42.523 --> 03:43.957
You got Villanuevaed.

03:49.062 --> 03:50.498
That's not true.

03:51.532 --> 03:53.000
Or even if it is a little true,

03:53.033 --> 03:55.403
I never would've worked
with Katherine long-term.

03:55.436 --> 03:57.671
Obviously, because
she's completely nuts.

03:57.705 --> 03:59.507
Oh, you don't think so?

03:59.540 --> 04:02.543
My sister tried to drown me
at sea. I have a high bar.

04:02.576 --> 04:03.611
NURSE:
All right.

04:03.644 --> 04:04.712
You are officially discharged.

04:04.745 --> 04:05.746
Wound care.

04:05.779 --> 04:07.448
Keep an eye on the color.

04:07.481 --> 04:09.317
We don't want to be
seeing green pus.

04:09.350 --> 04:10.551
We want to see red blood.

04:10.584 --> 04:13.687
This stuff is
terrific. Terrific!

04:13.721 --> 04:15.556
Please tell your dad thanks.

04:15.589 --> 04:17.725
Does he want to come,
by the way? Or your mom?

04:17.758 --> 04:19.460
We still have some
roles to assign.

04:19.493 --> 04:21.462
He'll be shooting,
but I'll ask my mom.

04:21.495 --> 04:24.598
Yeah, tell your grandma
to come, too.

04:24.632 --> 04:25.566
That's a great idea!

04:25.599 --> 04:26.867
We need a dowager.

04:26.900 --> 04:27.935
Seriously?

04:27.968 --> 04:30.771
Hey! So sorry
I'm late, babe.

04:30.804 --> 04:32.540
(laughing): Oh, my God.
Still with the "babe."

04:33.374 --> 04:35.643
I mean, nice to see you again.

04:35.676 --> 04:37.311
Don't mess things up this time.

04:37.345 --> 04:38.579
I'm trying
really hard not to.

04:38.612 --> 04:39.480
(laughs)

04:39.513 --> 04:41.415
Congratulations,
bride-to-be.

04:41.449 --> 04:42.483
Thank you.

04:42.516 --> 04:43.484
This is my fiancÃ©, Danny.

04:43.517 --> 04:44.652
Hey.
Hey.

04:44.685 --> 04:46.487
You look so familiar.

04:46.520 --> 04:48.055
Yeah, you do, too, actually.

04:48.088 --> 04:49.557
Did you ever live in New York?

04:49.590 --> 04:50.891
Yeah. Fort Greene.

04:50.924 --> 04:52.326
Oh, I had a bunch
of friends there.

04:52.360 --> 04:53.627
Uh, do you know
Joey Brixton?

04:53.661 --> 04:55.363
Jenny Lawson?
Mm...

04:55.396 --> 04:57.064
Let me check our mutuals.

04:57.097 --> 04:59.700
(quietly): See?
They're destined to be friends.

05:01.402 --> 05:02.536
Wait.

05:02.570 --> 05:05.539
Yeah, you two
used to date, right?

05:05.573 --> 05:06.740
Yeah.

05:06.774 --> 05:08.576
Ooh.

05:08.609 --> 05:12.012
Oh, sh-she's really pretty.

05:12.045 --> 05:13.414
Not her.

05:13.447 --> 05:15.549
Him.

05:15.583 --> 05:16.584
Oh.

05:17.685 --> 05:19.387
Cool.

05:19.420 --> 05:21.455
He's also very pretty.

05:28.729 --> 05:30.864
So, you're bisexual?

05:30.898 --> 05:32.866
If you're into labels.

05:32.900 --> 05:35.736
You date men and women?

05:35.769 --> 05:40.007
I had a boyfriend in art school
when everyone was experimenting,

05:40.040 --> 05:42.743
and another in Fort Greene
when everyone wasn't.

05:42.776 --> 05:45.112
Cool.

05:45.145 --> 05:47.715
It's just, we've had
so many long talks.

05:47.748 --> 05:49.783
How come you never
mentioned this?

05:49.817 --> 05:51.585
It just didn't really feel
that relevant.

05:51.619 --> 05:53.120
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR: I mean,
more relevant than who'd win

05:53.153 --> 05:55.556
in an epic battle between
Batman and Wolverine.

05:55.589 --> 05:57.658
Which has been
discussed at length.

05:57.691 --> 06:00.561
And I guess I was nervous.

06:00.594 --> 06:02.996
It's become an issue
with people I've dated before.

06:04.665 --> 06:07.668
Well, you've never
dated me before.

06:08.569 --> 06:09.703
Okay, you have.

06:09.737 --> 06:11.104
N-Not recently.

06:11.138 --> 06:12.740
My point is, is...

06:12.773 --> 06:14.708
(scoffs)
I'm totally okay with it.

06:14.742 --> 06:15.876
You have exes,
I have exes.

06:15.909 --> 06:17.478
Everybody has exes.
(chuckles)

06:17.511 --> 06:19.179
PETRA:
I'm trying, I'm trying!

06:19.212 --> 06:21.682
How hard can it be? Just...
(screams) Don't-don't pull!

06:21.715 --> 06:23.417
I'm sorry!
I'm just a little stressed.

06:23.451 --> 06:25.686
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
New role for Petra: nursemaid.

06:25.719 --> 06:27.421
Don't be. We're gonna
find another investor,

06:27.455 --> 06:29.557
and we'll make another offer.

06:29.590 --> 06:32.192
(knocking on door)
(scoffs) Unless Katherine
tells Luisa what we were doing.

06:32.225 --> 06:33.694
The woman already ran me over.

06:33.727 --> 06:35.763
I think she got her revenge.

06:35.796 --> 06:37.431
(scoffs)

06:37.465 --> 06:39.199
I know Rafael was working
with Katherine Cortes.

06:39.232 --> 06:41.535
Guess she wanted a little more.

06:41.569 --> 06:43.136
What are you doing
here? Security!

06:43.170 --> 06:46.006
Someone call security!
Luisa! Luisa!

06:46.039 --> 06:48.609
Rafael was just in an awful
car accident. Look at him.

06:48.642 --> 06:50.578
Please. Like I would ever

06:50.611 --> 06:53.046
fall for that.
It's obviously a sympathy ploy.

06:53.080 --> 06:54.014
(screams)

06:54.047 --> 06:55.449
What?
Ah. Oh.

06:55.483 --> 06:56.984
So it's not a sympathy ploy.
Luisa, please.

06:57.017 --> 06:58.719
Can he just stay here
till he gets better?

06:58.752 --> 07:00.020
Look, there's a guest room.

07:00.053 --> 07:01.789
No. And if you
ever step foot

07:01.822 --> 07:04.091
on my property again,
I will have you arrested.

07:04.124 --> 07:07.160
When did you become such
a nasty, hateful person...
Me? Me? No.

07:07.194 --> 07:08.696
...incapable of forgiveness
and compassion?!
You're the horrible person,

07:08.729 --> 07:10.764
Rafael. You can pretend
you're not, but you are.

07:10.798 --> 07:13.000
You're obsessed with money
and power, just like Dad.

07:13.033 --> 07:14.668
ELLIE:
Mommy!

07:15.669 --> 07:17.705
Everything's fine.

07:17.738 --> 07:19.673
Why don't you take the girls
down to the gift shop?

07:19.707 --> 07:22.075
We don't really need
another sparkly turtle.

07:22.109 --> 07:23.944
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Which brings us to...

07:23.977 --> 07:25.779
Alba.

07:25.813 --> 07:28.181
See, she, too,
plays many roles.

07:32.986 --> 07:34.688
Jorge's girlfriend.

07:35.689 --> 07:37.658
(gasps)
Hi, girls.

07:37.691 --> 07:39.026
What can I get for you?

07:39.059 --> 07:40.661
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Top merchandiser.

07:40.694 --> 07:42.930
Daddy's getting kicked
out of the hotel again,

07:42.963 --> 07:45.065
so we're supposed
to buy something.

07:48.602 --> 07:50.738
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
And captain of Team Rafael.

07:50.771 --> 07:52.773
(grunts)

07:54.074 --> 07:57.210
You said it was a
little car accident.

07:57.244 --> 07:58.846
Well, technically,
Petra said that.

07:58.879 --> 08:01.214
What happened, Daddy?

08:01.248 --> 08:04.518
I didn't look both ways
before I crossed the street.

08:13.961 --> 08:15.228
Hmm?

08:16.764 --> 08:18.732
What happened? Where were you?

08:18.766 --> 08:20.300
I broke up with Katherine.

08:20.333 --> 08:21.669
I told her
the truth,

08:21.702 --> 08:23.771
that I was using her,

08:23.804 --> 08:26.574
and she got pissed
and tried to run me over.

08:26.607 --> 08:28.208
What?

08:28.241 --> 08:31.311
Yeah. She's denying it,
but she did it on purpose.

08:31.344 --> 08:32.813
And yes,

08:32.846 --> 08:35.783
you were right. About her,
and about this whole thing

08:35.816 --> 08:37.951
being a bad idea,
but I really don't need

08:37.985 --> 08:39.620
"I told you so" right now, okay?

08:44.357 --> 08:46.627
(voice breaking):
Rafael.

08:47.828 --> 08:50.698
What has happened to you?

08:50.731 --> 08:52.600
To us?

08:52.633 --> 08:55.302
That you think
I would ever say that?

08:55.335 --> 08:56.870
I'm just happy
that you're okay,

08:56.904 --> 08:59.773
and I just really
want us to be okay.

08:59.807 --> 09:02.175
LATIN LOVER NARRATOR:
Yup. Just a fantasy.

09:02.209 --> 09:03.811
Here's what she really said.

09:03.844 --> 09:06.680
Well, let me know
if you need anything.

09:06.714 --> 09:07.881
I'm gonna go to bed.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.950
(inhales shakily)

09:14.788 --> 09:16.590
(doorbell rings)

09:18.125 --> 09:19.359
Hi.
Hi.

09:19.392 --> 09:20.894
(laughing):
Hey.
(laughs)

09:20.928 --> 09:22.262
Oh.
Hi.

09:22.295 --> 09:23.697
What's going on?

09:23.731 --> 09:25.599
I just wanted to stop by.

09:25.633 --> 09:26.934
Danny's at the airport,

09:26.967 --> 09:29.202
picking up some of his friends
for the party.

09:29.236 --> 09:31.605
Hmm. Oh. You okay?

09:31.639 --> 09:32.940
Totally, yes.

09:32.973 --> 09:33.874
But listen,
I'd love for you

09:33.907 --> 09:35.709
to spend some time
with Danny this weekend.

09:35.743 --> 09:36.777
One-on-one.

09:36.810 --> 09:37.845
Oh. Sure.

09:37.878 --> 09:39.613
I'd love to get
to know him better.

09:39.647 --> 09:41.048
Perfect. Great.

09:41.081 --> 09:42.883
Because I'm not sure
I should marry him,

09:42.916 --> 09:44.284
and I need you to tell me
what to do.

09:50.423 --> 09:53.393
Lina, back up.
Oh, God.

09:53.426 --> 09:54.394
What's going on?

09:54.427 --> 09:56.396
Did you and Danny fight?

09:56.429 --> 09:58.632
No. We never fight.

09:58.666 --> 10:00.133
And maybe that's part
of the problem.

10:00.167 --> 10:02.770
Uh, what problem?

10:02.803 --> 10:04.772
Where is this
even coming from?

10:04.805 --> 10:06.940
My sisters staged
an intervention.

10:06.974 --> 10:09.142
They are convinced that
I'm making a mistake.

10:09.176 --> 10:11.679
They think I'll be
divorced by Christmas.

10:11.712 --> 10:13.246
A-And what if
they're right?

10:13.280 --> 10:14.648
They know me.

10:14.682 --> 10:16.116
And they've all
been divorced.

10:16.149 --> 10:17.985
Which just means they picked
badly for themselves,

10:18.018 --> 10:19.653
not that you did.

10:19.687 --> 10:21.288
Come on. You fell in love
with Danny for a reason.

10:21.321 --> 10:23.256
What are some of the things
you love about him?

10:23.290 --> 10:25.192
Well, he's-he's so sweet,

10:25.225 --> 10:28.161
and smart and so supportive.

10:28.195 --> 10:29.396
Plus, he's great in bed.

10:29.429 --> 10:31.965
God, what a nightmare.
You poor thing.

10:31.999 --> 10:33.433
But he's such a
square sometimes.

10:33.466 --> 10:34.802
What do you mean?

10:34.835 --> 10:37.204
He has bisexual friends
from Fort Greene.

10:37.237 --> 10:40.173
This murder mystery theme?

10:40.207 --> 10:41.675
It was supposed to be

10:41.709 --> 10:44.344
a bachelor/bachelorette party.

10:44.377 --> 10:47.280
Why would he think that I would
like something like that?

10:47.314 --> 10:49.717
I don't want to have to learn
a bunch of new words

10:49.750 --> 10:50.684
for my bachelorette party.

10:50.718 --> 10:52.720
What the hell is
a dowager?!

10:52.753 --> 10:55.723
A widow who got her title
from her late husband.

10:55.756 --> 10:58.859
Look, Lina, I was...

10:58.892 --> 11:00.293
surprised by the theme, too.

11:00.327 --> 11:03.731
See? And, Jane,
he likes to ski.

11:03.764 --> 11:06.133
You know how much
I hate the cold.

11:06.166 --> 11:08.435
Plus, he doesn't have
a spontaneous bone in his body.

11:08.468 --> 11:10.470
What if I want us
to quit our jobs

11:10.503 --> 11:11.905
and travel the world
for a year?

11:11.939 --> 11:13.907
I mean, do you?

11:13.941 --> 11:16.710
Assuming it's
first-class airfare

11:16.744 --> 11:19.246
and five-star hotels,
which he would never go for

11:19.279 --> 11:21.481
because he's so
freaking practical!

11:21.514 --> 11:22.950
Okay, you're spiraling.

11:22.983 --> 11:24.818
I know.

11:24.852 --> 11:27.721
Which is why I need you
to tell me what to do.

11:27.755 --> 11:30.290
XIOMARA: Not your place,
and not your role.

11:30.323 --> 11:32.259
Just tell Lina
that Danny is great,

11:32.292 --> 11:34.061
and you're completely
on board with the two of them.

11:34.094 --> 11:36.764
It's just the two of us.
No Baby.

11:36.797 --> 11:37.998
JANE:
But she asked for my help.

11:38.031 --> 11:39.967
I mean,
don't I owe it to her

11:40.000 --> 11:41.969
to give my honest opinion
no matter what?

11:42.002 --> 11:43.937
If you want to stay friends
with her, no.

11:43.971 --> 11:45.739
I absolutely want
to stay friends with you.

11:45.773 --> 11:46.940
Sexy friends.

11:46.974 --> 11:49.109
Tell Dad I can hear him.

11:50.177 --> 11:51.945
It's a lose-lose

11:51.979 --> 11:54.014
situation, Janie.

11:54.047 --> 11:55.115
If you say he sucks,

11:55.148 --> 11:56.183
and she marries him anyway,

11:56.216 --> 11:58.018
